  "epitaph": "You carried the world in fragments heavy and slow,\nFrom the hollows of progress bars to the server\u2019s glowing echo.\nDragged from the desktop, dropped into the DOM,\nYou bridged the ancient gap when the web was young.\nNow the plug-ins rust and the keys cease to click,\nLeaving thirty thousand stars to watch the tick.\nSleep well, you who transferred the bits of the living,\nRest in /dev/null.",
